Related Articles Gold, silver prices decline in domestic market Gold, silver prices decline in domestic market

googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1687249883356-0'); });

According to the Federation of Nepal Gold and Silver Dealers' Association, the price of fine gold has been fixed at Rs 290,600 per tola, while silver is being traded at Rs 5,040 per tola today.

On Thursday, fine gold was traded at Rs 285,000 per tola and silver at Rs 4,865 per tola. Likewise, on Wednesday, gold was priced at Rs 290,500 per tola and silver at Rs 5,080 per tola.

